The Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi, Ojaja II, has proceeded on a seven-day annual seclusion as this year’s edition of the Olojo festival begins in Ile Ife, Osun State. On Sunday evening, before the ceremonies for his seclusion, the foremost traditional ruler and the Arole Oodua addressed reporters, hailing the formal commencement of the Olojo festival. He said he was in high spirits to meet with “God Almighty who owns the day through fasting and prayers’’. The Ooni said he would pray for the resuscitation of the country’s economy while in seclusion.